# Unsupervised clustering of donor phenotypes (ORCHID)

## Overview
This project applies unsupervised learning to identify physiological donor phenotypes and evaluate their association with procurement and transplantation outcomes.

## Key finding
Donors with similar physiological profiles may experience different outcomes, suggesting system-level variability beyond measurable biology.

## Methods
K-means, GMM, UMAP, logistic regression, random forest (Python).

## Data
ORCHID dataset (PhysioNet, credentialed access required).

